Package wrapScienceJ.metaData.container

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MetaDataParser  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    MetaData
    This class is intended to contain metadata information regarding an image.
    MetaDataContainer
    Allows to represent a collection of parameters for use as input of a Generic Process.
    MetaDataParserFile
    Allows to read the configuration parameters for a Generic Process by parsing a Config File.
    MetaDataRetriever
    Allows to retrieve metadata from several sources according to a policy.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    MetaDataContainer.UpdatePolicy
    The policy for managing and updating configs can be "overwrite": An existing config is overwritten if a new config is obtained; "Always ask": A new configuration is sought at each invocation without changing the default config (the GenericProcessConfig.duplicate() method can be used) "Always use default": No configuration input is sought at all and the configuration is taken as is, assumed to be "one size fits all"
    MetaDataRetriever.RetrievalPolicy
    Enumeration of all possible options ID for wrapImaJ implementers.
